  "text": "where f w (θ) is the wrapped PDF of θ on [0, π]. Proof: The proof is given in Appendix E. At present no further convenient analysis for H v (z 1 , z 2 ) appears tractable and we leave the representation in Lemma 3 as a single finite range numeric integral. Substituting the results of Lemmas 1, 2 and 3 in (30), [CITATION_1] and (32), respectively, gives κ which completes the derivation of (20) and [CITATION_2] . As for the ULA, we note that summation over n can be truncated with very few terms as the ψ(n) coefficients decay very rapidly. In Appendix F we prove the convergence of the series in Lemmas 1, 2, and 3 and also derive bounds on the truncation error of these series. This allows us to select the number of terms in the truncated series to guarantee any desired accuracy.",
